<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-05-22T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-05-22T05:00:00-05:00" n="108" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d108">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">340.1115A/667: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bern</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-05-22T11:00:00+01:00">May
                                        22, 1940—11 a.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received May 22—8:36 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>46. Department’s 55, May 21. American citizens with valid passports
                                able to proceed promptly to Genoa from Switzerland to return to the
                                United States. No Swiss exit visas or Italian entrance and exit
                                visas required for American citizens. Through car rail connections
                                between Zurich and Genoa re-established yesterday via Saint
                                Gotthard. Convenient connections also between Bern, Geneva, Lausanne
                                and <pb facs="0110" n="101" xml:id="pg_101"/> Genoa via Simplon with
                                single change at Milan. Duration of journey Bern Genoa 9½ hours.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Harrison</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>